  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he refused to listen and said that he didn't trust the Russians any more than the Germans and would not return and didn't return with them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he and this friend didn't come back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was a blow to my mother, of course, and to me by transmittal of her feelings that my father was still off somewhere unbeknownst to anyone where.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had lived in Lithuania is what we were told by the others, sometimes in the forests, sometimes near Kovno, hiding most of the time, and that he was going to probably continue that existence but where, when, and what he was doing right then and there, nobody knew.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Of course what happened is a [SIGHS] really another turning point in our lives, is that within 24 hours of the Russian return, all of the people who were city councilmen that had returned to Bialystok were arrested by the what is now the KGB-- it was the NKVD at that time-- and sent off to Siberia, some of them perishing along the way.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, again, my father had made the right decision.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Had he returned, he was surely going to be arrested because the NKVD came to look for him to arrest him.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
